# Rule 6: Ransomware-Like File Modification
# --------------------------------------------------
# Description: Detects rapid file modification or renaming to known ransomware extensions 
# within a short period. This rule focuses on data encryption behavior.
# 
# MITRE ATT&CK: T1486 (Data Encrypted for Impact)
# Severity: Critical
# 
# Logic (Behavioral):
#   - EventID: 4663 (An attempt was made to access an object)
#   - AccessMask: 0x2 (WriteData / AddFile)
#   - Extension matches: ('.locky', '.encrypted', '.crypt', '.crypted', '.wannacry')
#   - Threshold: Count > 50 events within 1 minute from the same Source User.
# 
# Log Source: Windows Security Log (Object Access: File System)
